Family Bank Has Recorded A 1.01 Billion Profit Before Tax In The 9 Months Of 2019 Trading Results. The Bank Has Attributed The Improved Performance To A Surge In In Loans Which Has Been Bolstered By Growth In Customer Deposits And Growth In Operating Income. With The Removal Of The Interest Rate Cap By The Government, The Bank’s Chairman Dr. Wilfred Kiboro Says That They Are Not Going To Introduce New Interest Rates Any Time Soon Despite Some Banks Having Come Under Pressure To Revise The Rates Upwards.